<br>
I barely have the CPU to handle the turtles in Twilight Sea, but they're great XP for this level, and few people camp them. I pull them in the same fashion as the bloodgills and they never run out. They're not as often camped either.<br>
<br>
If a druid is at the turtles, Scarlet desert (if those lightcrawlers weren't so stubborn and anarchaic in nature) would be my place to attempt quads. There are other scattered social mobs that occasionally can make a quad. My quadding experience here is limited, and i've made a couple on the fly that have worked. It ussually takes me 4 near-zone quad attempts that fail to get one that works well. - <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Stay away from cheetahs.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
____<br>
At 47:<br>
<br>
I level now when I can get KEI and my wizard is staged so that he can play or I can plan play-time for him for the 2 and a half hours KEI lasts to get the full use of it. This speeds up the time I'm spending here (at least 1 bub an hour), and makes it available quicker (and absolute) to someone who might want to XP Grind there instead. <br>
<br>
When I can't get one of these three places, its time to do something different (and SD is really stretching it). At this point, I log off and play an alt. My bard on Druzzil is building up cobwebs, but I just started a Necro wiz on Rallos now, and a wizard on Vazaelle (heh.)<br>
<br>
<br>
From my experiences in playing a number of charactars, if you have them its nice to stage them all in different scenarios. <br>
<br>
<br>
A &quot;PK&quot; on one of the Zeks planted at CB, Kurn's Tower, or Highpass Hold lets me see some different sort of strategies from the other side of the table.<br>
<br>
My bard on Druzzil is the &quot;group leader&quot; and gets things done by filling in holes in groups. I loved taking a group of fresh charactars through and &quot;doing&quot; CB at early levels, and clearing drolvarg shrines in Firiona Vie just so the group could say they saw the back of it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
